{"TopicId":167374,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How to view CoM and CoT in flight?","CreatedByName":"Mine_Turtle","CreatedById":163953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T18:45:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mine_Turtle","CreatedById":163953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T18:45:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have 4 engines in cross formation, that allow me to change \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E to minimize vessel tendency to rotation during acceleration. However, I do not know of a way to visualize those centers in flight. I have VesselViewer installed, but it only shows center of mass. Any other method to visualize \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E in flight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-09T21:28:19Z\u0022 title=\u002211/09/2017 09:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Mine_Turtle\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T20:08:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModding question moved to the modding subforum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mine_Turtle","CreatedById":163953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T21:39:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215120\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510258116\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModding question moved to the modding subforum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002227914\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vanamonde\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E ,\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EHow is this a modding question? This a gameplay question:\u00A0 I am looking for any method: stock or mod to help me balance my engine setup vs \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-09T21:40:58Z\u0022 title=\u002211/09/2017 09:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Mine_Turtle\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T22:08:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably because there isnt a stock way to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would suggest looking at Throttle Controlled Avionics mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-09T22:37:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510263573\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163953\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mine_Turtle\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, Mine_Turtle said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002227914\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vanamonde\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E ,\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EHow is this a modding question? This a gameplay question:\u00A0 I am looking for any method: stock or mod to help me balance my engine setup vs \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry I wasn\u0027t clear. There is no method in stock, but there might be a mod which does it, so it seemed you were more likely to get a helpful answer in this subforum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mine_Turtle","CreatedById":163953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T05:27:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215274\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510265330\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably because there isnt a stock way to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would suggest looking at Throttle Controlled Avionics mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not entirely agree that there is no stock way. So far, I have been using very stock method - eyeballing: observe how much pitch and yaw \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E uses during acceleration and compensate with engine thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou were right about TCA though, I had the mod installed for long time but was assuming it is primarily used to flying VTOLs. As of now my station is accelerating without having problems with engine torque. Thanks for the suggestion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T06:41:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI sometime put markers on my craft for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E, just an\u00A0antenna recessed almost completely into the craft at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E. you could do the same for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E (several of you have multiple set CoTs).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E it\u0027s a bit less precise but the camera focuses on the crafts \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E so by zooming in while looking directly down on the craft\u00A0you can get a ruff idea where \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T11:26:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510291647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163953\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mine_Turtle\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Mine_Turtle said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not entirely agree that there is no stock way. So far, I have been using very stock method - eyeballing: observe how much pitch and yaw \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E uses during acceleration and compensate with engine thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510296102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002235181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022katateochi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, katateochi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI sometime put markers on my craft for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E, just an\u00A0antenna recessed almost completely into the craft at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E. you could do the same for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E (several of you have multiple set CoTs).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E it\u0027s a bit less precise but the camera focuses on the crafts \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E so by zooming in while looking directly down on the craft\u00A0you can get a ruff idea where \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth fair enough ways of doing it, but my impression was that he wanted something like the visual markers which are available in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Theysen","CreatedById":144656,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T12:57:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechjeb can show those balls IIRC.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT:\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYES - And they also move fluently while having them activated.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is under Attitude Adjustement -\u0026gt; show \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL and it also has Vectors for surface speed, orbital speed direction etc \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-10T13:04:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/10/2017 01:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Theysen\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mine_Turtle","CreatedById":163953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T20:40:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223215752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510318639\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144656\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Theysen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Theysen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechjeb can show those balls IIRC.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT:\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYES - And they also move fluently while having them activated.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is under Attitude Adjustement -\u0026gt; show \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL and it also has Vectors for surface speed, orbital speed direction etc \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you. That is exactly what I was looking for initially. However, as I realized TCA does the job of balancing engine thrust way better then I could hope for with a naked eye.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-10T21:40:10Z\u0022 title=\u002211/10/2017 09:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Mine_Turtle\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skalou","CreatedById":133496,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T21:52:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere is the mod FlightMarkers too ( splitted from the original Collide-o-Scope mod)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/flightmarkers\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/flightmarkers\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022flightmarkers-image3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022705\u0022 src=\u0022https://media-elerium.cursecdn.com/attachments/219/405/flightmarkers-image3.jpg\u0022 style=\u0022width:400px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022953\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-10T21:53:00Z\u0022 title=\u002211/10/2017 09:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Skalou\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}